# 🚀 Day 7 – Host a Static Website on AWS EC2 using Apache HTTP Server

## 📌 Project Overview
In this project, I deployed a static website on an Amazon EC2 instance using the Apache HTTP Server (httpd). The website is accessible over the internet through the EC2 Public IP.

## 🎯 Objective
- Launch an EC2 instance
- Install and configure Apache HTTP Server
- Deploy a static HTML website
- Configure Security Groups to allow HTTP traffic
- Access the website using the EC2 Public IP

## 🛠️ AWS Services Used
- Amazon EC2
- Security Groups
- Apache HTTP Server (httpd)

## 📋 Steps Performed
1. Launched an Amazon Linux 2023 EC2 instance.
2. Connected to the instance using SSH (PuTTY).
3. Updated system packages.
4. Installed Apache HTTP Server.
5. Started and enabled the Apache service.
6. Created a custom `index.html` webpage.
7. Configured the Security Group to allow HTTP (Port 80).
8. Verified the website using the EC2 Public IP.

## 💻 Commands Used

```bash
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
sudo systemctl status httpd
```

